sect1.para:
Jails are often started at boot time and the &os;
      rc mechanism provides an easy way to do
      this.

Jails can be shut down with &man.jexec.8;.  Use &man.jls.8;
      to identify the jail's JID, then use
      &man.jexec.8; to run the shutdown script in that jail.

example.programlisting:
...
// or cause huge amounts of useless Internet traffic.

acl "trusted" {
	192.168.1.0/24;
	localhost;
	localnets;
};

options {
...

forwarders {
	10.0.0.62;
	10.0.0.61;
};

allow-query       { any; };
allow-recursion   { trusted; };
allow-query-cache { trusted; };
